          <source>ON_UPDATE_COMMAND_UI Macro</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Properties<ept id="p1">**</ept> window to connect a user-interface object to a command-update handler in a command-target object.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>It will automatically connect the user-interface object's ID to the <ph id="ph1">`ON_UPDATE_COMMAND_UI`</ph> macro and create a handler in the object that will handle the update.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>See <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>Mapping Messages to Functions<ept id="p1">](../mfc/reference/mapping-messages-to-functions.md)</ept> for more information.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, to update a Clear All command in your program's Edit menu, use the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Properties<ept id="p1">**</ept> window to add a message-map entry in the chosen class, a function declaration for a command-update handler called <ph id="ph1">`OnUpdateEditClearAll`</ph> in the class declaration, and an empty function template in the class's implementation file.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The function prototype looks like this:</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>NVC_MFCDocView#2</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Like all handlers, the function shows the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>afx_msg<ept id="p1">**</ept> keyword.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Like all update handlers, it takes one argument, a pointer to a <ph id="ph1">`CCmdUI`</ph> object.</source>
        </trans-unit>
